    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.13/30.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>There is a movement to secure the pardon of Asbert alone, through amnesty
                    proceedings, the contention being that Arias admitted killing Rivas and there is
                    no doubt of Asbert’s guilt. I assume Department is not interested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
